MESSAGE.value: added States to avoid generics hell in future unit tests. small renamings and reorderings.
split into core and example modules in preparation for release
fixed module dependencies
example is now in the validation package. yet another package rename!
classes that don't need to be public, aren't. removed describeTo(List<ValidationError>)
reformated code and optimised imports
added apache license 2.0.
moved classes into java directories. added build script to build core.
formatted the readme
added StateRelationships for resolving state dependencies using a predefined tree. added StateGraph for resolving state dependencies in a directed acyclic graph format
refactored the StateGraph into States and made some internal improvements
added missing class
integrated States into example
added an import
removed old way of doing state dependencies
fixed those annoying intellij errors i've been getting with Matchers.hasSize on a Map<String, String>
changed example concept from a pizza order to a login. whole project can be built now. added getters to Field. changed Matcher generics to be compatible with hamcrest matchers.
moved LoginState inside Login
replaced implementation of Field with an interface called DescribableField
created Password and UserName classes because Login was doing too much. Removed some unused libraries from the lib folder
extracted MessageFilteringMessageWriter from ModelMapErrorMessageWriter
moved the MessageFilteringMessageWriter to validation.core
small clean up
more code clean up
removed unnecessary intellij file from version control
